criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  seeing a VA Connecticut mental health clinician at least 3 times in the past 3 months
             with intent to remain in treatment during study enrollment;

          -  age 18 and over;

          -  social dysfunction (score > 3 on the Social Adjustment Scale-Self Report (SAS-SR) and
             > 2 on Inventory of Interpersonal Problems-32 (IIP-32);

          -  emotion dysregulation (score > 105 on the Difficulties in Emotion Regulation Scale
             (DERS);

          -  sufficient mobility to participate in study procedures, as determined by PI;

          -  consent to all study procedures, including audio recording of TEE and AC sessions.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  psychotic disorder per self-report and verified in medical record or as determined by
             the Mini-International Neuropsychiatric Interview (MINI);

          -  acute suicidality;

          -  inability to read English or communicate in spoken English;

          -  anticipated unavailability to the study during the next 20 weeks;

          -  participation in any equine-facilitated therapy in the past 24 weeks;

          -  unavailability of a landline or cellular telephone.
